r pound in north america effective september   or as contracts allow € per metric ton in european middle eastern and african markets effective october   or as contracts allow and us per metric ton in asia pacific and latin american markets effective october   or as contracts allow about tronoxtronox limited is a global leader in the mining production and marketing of inorganic minerals and chemicals the company operates two vertically integrated businesses tronox titanium dioxide tio and tronox alkali for more information visit wwwtronoxcom media contact bud grebeydirect  investor contact brennen arndtdirect  logo  httpphotosprnewswirecomprnhdalogo   to view the original version on pr newswire visithttpwwwprnewswirecomnewsreleasestronoxannouncestiopriceincreaseshtml source tronox limited news provided by acquire media q  earnings call  tronox limited tronox alkali tronox titanium dioxide regional web sites botlek netherlands perth australia our company products tronox titanium dioxide mineral sands titanium dioxide pigment tronox alkali electrolytic and specialty chemicals investor relations newsroom sustainability careers q  earnings call aug    am et listen to webcast view presentation  kb add to briefcase file is in briefcase investor relations press releases events and presentations corporate governanceraquo corporate governance home management board of directors committee composition contact the board recent financial informationraquo financial information home quarterly results sec filings annual reports and proxies stock informationraquo stock information historical stock prices investment calculator analyst coverage tronox warrants contact us  tronox limited all rights reserved privacy policy  terms of use  site map  contact us tronox  wikipedia tronox from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search tronox corporation logo tronox limited nyse trox is an american worldwide chemical company involved in the titanium products industry with approximately  employees following its acquisition of the mineral sands business formerly belonging to south africa’s exxaro resources tronox is the largest fully integrated seller and marketer of titanium dioxide tio pigment which provides brightness to applications such as coatings plastics and paper tronox also sells titanium ore – the main feedstock of titanium dioxide  and zircon directly to customers tronox is the thirdlargest titanium feedstock producer with approximately  of global titanium ore production and the secondlargest producer of zircon with approximately  of global production the company also has an electrolytic and speciality chemicals business that services the paper and battery industries formerly a part of the kerrmcgee chemical corporation and based in oklahoma city since it was spun off from its parent in  the company announced in june  that it was moving its headquarters to stamford connecticut the company was spun off in part to offload its parent company kerrmcgees legacy of generations of environmental dumping of toxic waste across  states according to one report kerrmcgee rather than pay for the environmental mess it created decided to shift the liabilities between  and  into tronox kerrmcgee meanwhile kept its valuable oil and gas assets tronox did not reveal the massive hidden liabilities to investors and after they became known tronox dropped to a penny stock in  in response shareholders sued anadarko petroleum corporation successor to kerrmcgee for keeping the scope of the environmental disaster a secret in addition the us federal government sued anadarko to pay for the cleanup and in april  settled on the largest environmental contamination settlement in american history over  billion contents  history  locations  kerrmcgee spinoff  see also  references  external links historyedit the company went public in  when oklahoma citybased kerrmcgee which had previously owned the company entirely issued shares via an ipo on november   it became an independent company in march  in the first quarter of  tronox replaced meade instruments on the sp smallcap  index when kerrmcgee distributed the rest of its stock in tronox under its former nyse symbol trxb a class b security trxb started regularway trading on march   in  the companys stock price declined significantly and both classes of stock became penny stocks in september  the companys stock moved from the nyse to otc on  january  tronox filed chapter  bankruptcy it specified that this action did not include the companys nonusa operations in  shareholders of tronox sued anadarko petroleum corporation successor to kerrmcgee for having misled investors about the large environmental and other debts tronox would inherit from its parent corporation the environmental pollution included polluting lake mead in nevada with rocket fuel leaving behind radioactive waste piles throughout the territory of the navajo nation and dumping carcinogenic creosote in communities throughout the east midwest and south at its woodtreating facilities in  the huntsman corporation announced it would buy certain of tronoxs assets such as its factories in late  tronox terminated this deal tronox emerged from chapter  bankruptcy on february   tom casey became ceo in october  on june   tronox announced that it had completed the acquisition of exxaro mineral sands and combined both entities under tronox limited an australian holding company describing the benefits of the combination tronox limited ceo tom casey said we now have the ability to sell into a lucrative titanium feedstock market while assuring our titanium dioxide customers that we have the supply to deliver quality products at reasonable prices” in april  the federal government reached a  billion settlement with anadarko successor to kerrmcgee in the largest environmental contamination case in american history according to one report kerrmcgee rather than pay for the environmental mess it created decided to shift the liabilities between  and  into tronox kerrmcgee meanwhile kept its valuable oil and gas assets the cost to clean up the mess inherited by tronox from kerrmcgee was estimated by the courts to be over  billion there are contaminated sites in  states and the navajo nation among the dozens of locations targeted for cleanup under the settlement is a former chemical manufacturing site in nevada that has led to contamination in lake mead abandoned uranium mines in and around the navajo nation and a superfund site in gloucester nj polluted by thorium locationsedit global headquarters stamford connecticut mineral sands operations namakwa sands south africa kwazulunatal kzn sands south africa cooljarloo western australia chandala processing plant western australia pigment productions hamilton mississippi botlek netherlands kwinana australia electrolyic operations henderson nevada hamilton mississippi kerrmcgee spinoffedit kerrmcgee spun off its chemical business circa  after demands were made by corporate raider and major kerrmcgee shareholder carl icahn among other things tronox inherited several radioactive waste sites from kerrmcgee these include the cimarron fuel fabrication site and the rare earths facility they are as of  still undergoing cleanup it also inherited the henderson nevada bmi site this site had supplied magnesium and other chemicals beginning around world war ii it eventually leaked perchlorate used in rocket fuel into the water table which subsequently contaminated lake mead and the colorado river which supply water to millions of people exiting bankruptcy in february  tronoxs chapter  plan created the anadarko litigation trust to pursue tronoxs lawsuit against anadarko and kerrmcgee tronox has transferred an  share of its interest in the lawsuit to the federal government see alsoedit covington  burling advised during spinoffipo referencesedit  mara lee with  million state lures chemical firm mired in pollution disputes hartford courant june    tronox to receive  million in settlement with united states tronox retrieved    tronox  annual report pdf  retrieved    a b c d e f eric tucker april   us reaches  billion environmental settlement ap retrieved april     kerrmcgee launches tronox ipo in us raises m  november  icis news brian ford  tronox incorporated becomes independent company thomas w adams named chairman and chief executive officer tronoxcom media news archive     tronox chapter  petition pdf pacermonitor pacermonitor retrieved  june    chemical  engineering news  jan  pigment maker tronox files for bankruptcy p   al greenwood may  anadarko denies role in bankrupt tronox fraud lawsuit icis  reed business information ltd retrieved    shareholder class action filed on behalf of purchasers of tronox inc by the law firm of barroway topaz kessler meltzer  check llp prnewswire  reuters  retrieved    tronox faq tronox archived from the original on  retrieved    tronox inc wants day in court with kerrmcgee corp the journal record oklahoma city may   by marie price  tronox cancels asset sale to huntsman the associated press december   ap  huntsman to buy most of tronox alexander h tullo chemical and engineering news     tronox appoints tom casey ceo tronoxcom october    tronox announces closing of exxaro mineral sands acquisition  tronoxcom june    kerrmcgee caves in to icahn by ray tyson petroleum news  apr   kerrmcgee  cimarron us nrc april  retrieved    us environmental protection agency jul  npl fact sheet kerrmcgee sewage treatment plant archived from the original on  retrieved    remediation of the bmi complex state of nevada division of environmental protection website accessed     final report the fate and transport of perchlorate in a contaminated site in the las vegas valley us environmental protection agency batista amy chen papelis and unz   update tronox anadarko restart settlement talks trial on hold wall street journal     httpwwwcovcomfilesnewsdfaadedbpresentationnewsattachmentaaecfdeeboidpdf covington advises ke