d businesses titanium dioxide tio and alkali with decades of experience and success we look for talented individuals to join our team our global production facilities and sales organizations are strategically located to serve customers in more than  countries we recruit people with the expertise and drive to meet our customers’ needs around the world in careers including plant operations and maintenance research and development chemists scientists technicians plant engineering chemical process engineers sales and marketing customer service safety health and environment business development supply chain management human resources and communications information technology finance  accountingtreasuryfinancial reporting administration continuous learning to encourage employees to reach their full potential and for tronox to act as a catalyst to enhance employees abilities professionally and personally we offer an educational assistance program to gain a desired degree or certification related to their field equal opportunity employer tronox is an equal opportunity employer and does not discriminate based on race gender religion national origin age disability veteran status or citizenship diversity “first and foremost we support diversity because it is the right thing to do we live in a diverse world we work in diverse communities and talent and commitment come in all colors genders shapes and sizes we want our work force to reflect the world we live in diversity is also good business practice because it has been proven in many industries to be a powerful tool for generating innovation strong business performance and growth into new markets at tronox we aspire not only to build a diverse workforce but to leverage the broad range of people and perspectives within our organization by fostering an inclusive work environment these twin social goals are and will continue to be the catalyst of the financial success of our company” tom casey chairman and ceo australia opportuni